1
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:20,353
- [ringing]
- [Boyd] Previously on From...

2
00:00:20,437 --> 00:00:22,105
All you fucking do

3
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:26,985
is knock on our doors,
knock on our fucking windows!

4
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:29,821
You wanna play games?
Come get me!

5
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:32,490
[grunts]

6
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:35,827
My blood is your blood now,
motherfucker.

7
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,746
[screeches]

8
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,956
You really did it.
You killed one of them.

9
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,295
All this time, I thought

10
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,047
the children were trying
to scare me, but...

11
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,631
what if they're just
asking for my help?

12
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,051
So Victor said his mother
wanted to rescue the children

13
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,177
locked in the tower.

14
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,095
I'm sorry. This is the only way.

15
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:57,223
[screaming]

16
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:58,892
Are you deaf?
I said, get the--

17
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:00,477
Where did you get that?

18
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,896
You're Victor's father.

19
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:04,898
[Henry] My wife, Miranda,
started seeing things.

20
00:01:04,981 --> 00:01:06,900
She said it was like

21
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:10,570
she'd been chosen
to free the children.

22
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:14,491
- [screaming]
- [horn honks]

23
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:17,118
But there's a town up ahead!

24
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,536
You just need to keep
going forward! Please!

25
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:21,915
- [screeches]
- [groans]

26
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,211
Victor.

27
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:28,588
I didn't know
how to get home.

28
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:32,926
The Boy in White
was trying to tell Christopher

29
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:34,386
that to save the children,

30
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:36,471
he would have
to go through the tree.

31
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:38,348
Christopher
wouldn't go through the tree,

32
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:41,434
so I told my mother
what the Boy in White said.

33
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:42,977
It was my fault.

34
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:44,896
I was the reason
that she died.

35
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:46,981
She was trying
to protect you.

36
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:49,109
That's my job now.

37
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:50,860
We thought you were dead.

38
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:53,571
Your children
thought you were dead.

39
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:55,532
You owe it to your kids
to be here now.

40
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:58,827
This place wants us
to be scared.

41
00:01:58,910 --> 00:02:01,746
How we take care of each other
and how we always do our best,

42
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,623
that's what matters.

43
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,959
- You're not pregnant.
- I am pregnant!

44
00:02:06,042 --> 00:02:07,627
I can feel it!

45
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:10,296
I'm not eating garbage 
because I'm afraid!

46
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,798
It's making me!

47
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:15,301
Whatever is inside me,
it's getting stronger.

48
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:18,471
Help me, Elgin.
I can save all of you.

49
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,515
I can help you go back home.

50
00:02:20,598 --> 00:02:22,559
[Fatima] Elgin, please!

51
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:25,895
Fatima's baby
is going to save all of us.

52
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,480
He's not gonna
tell you where she is.

53
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:30,275
You said that you weren't
gonna let this place break you.

54
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,319
This place has won.

55
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,781
[screaming]

56
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:38,241
What the fuck are you doing?

57
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:42,203
Boyd doesn't understand
how far he needs to go.

58
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,706
- Sara--
- She's in the root cellar.

59
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:47,334
[Boyd] I'm not gonna be 
 blindsided by this place again.

60
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:49,586
I need to see it.

61
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,713
[Fatima] Those things
that come out at night,

62
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:55,175
they sacrificed their children,
because It promised them

63
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:57,260
that they would live forever.

64
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:05,143
[Jade] Miranda had visions
of this place.

65
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:07,228
She's the only one who had
a connection to this place

66
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,396
long before she arrived.

67
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,065
It wasn't just Miranda.

68
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,735
When I was a little girl, 
I saw this place, too.

69
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:18,365
[violin playing mournful tune]

70
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:19,657
Anghkooey.

71
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,159
Remember.

72
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:22,869
Oh, God.

73
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:25,330
The reason I felt
what Miranda felt

74
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:27,999
is because I was Miranda.

75
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:30,794
And Jade was Christopher.
We've come back

76
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:33,838
over and over again because
we failed the first time.

77
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:36,925
I need some time, honey.

78
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,761
[Julie]
 When I walked inside the ruins,

79
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:41,638
suddenly, 
I was in a chamber.

80
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:42,639
[screaming]

81
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,015
I think I was actually there.

82
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:45,767
You're a Storywalker.

83
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:47,686
 Someone who can visit chapters

84
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:49,020
of the story 
that already happened.

85
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,146
What?

86
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,690
But you can't change them.

87
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,650
Dad!
I think this is when it happens!

88
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,193
- Slow down.
- No, no, listen to me!

89
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,320
I need to change
the story, Dad, please!

90
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:59,781
That was a hell of a song.

91
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:01,991
This didn't have
to happen, you know.

92
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,035
Knowledge comes with a cost.

93
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:06,246
[choking]

94
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,456
Your wife shouldn't
have dug that hole, Jim.

95
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,708
[choking]

96
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:14,587
No!

97
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,925
[screaming]

98
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:24,305
[sighs]
People are such fragile things.

99
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:27,809
We have to stop
meeting like this.

100
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:29,477
When did you
come from this time?

101
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:30,854
[gasping]

102
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,106
Didn't anyone tell ya?

103
00:04:33,189 --> 00:04:36,234
There's no way to change
a story once it's been told.

104
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,363
[sighs]

105
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,163
Just you and me now, Jim.

106
00:04:50,165 --> 00:04:54,461
I liked you. I really did.

107
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,296
[whispered] Fuck you.

108
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:59,632
[chuckles]
You always tried so hard.

109
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:03,428
You carried so much.

110
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:09,059
It's a terrible shame you won't
get to see what happens next.

111
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:12,729
Because what happens next...

112
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:14,981
is my favorite part.

113
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:19,194
Would you like to know why?

114
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:22,364
[chuckles]

115
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:26,701
[ominous music]

116
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,255
[sighs]

117
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:54,479
["Que Sera, Sera (Whatever Will
Be, Will Be)" plays]

118
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:04,406
♪ When I was just a little boy ♪

119
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:06,825
♪ I asked my father ♪

120
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:09,035
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

121
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,914
♪ "Will I be handsome?" ♪

122
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:15,417
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

123
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:19,337
♪ Here's what he said to me ♪

124
00:06:19,421 --> 00:06:22,882
♪ Que sera sera ♪

125
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,803
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

126
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:32,642
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

127
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:35,353
♪ Que sera sera ♪

128
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:40,525
♪ What will be will be ♪

129
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:54,914
♪ Now I have 
children of my own ♪

130
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:57,334
♪ They ask their father ♪

131
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:01,004
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

132
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,548
♪ "Will I be pretty?" ♪

133
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:05,925
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

134
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:09,846
♪ I tell them tenderly ♪

135
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,474
♪ Que sera sera ♪

136
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:18,229
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

137
00:07:19,064 --> 00:07:23,068
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

138
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:26,237
♪ Que sera sera ♪

139
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,618
♪ What will be will be ♪

140
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:36,164
♪ Que sera sera ♪

141
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:53,014
What do you mean, they
sacrificed their children?

142
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:55,058
[breathing heavily]

143
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:59,688
Those things in the woods.
They were people once.

144
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:02,148
They made a--

145
00:08:02,232 --> 00:08:07,112
a bargain
with something horrible.

146
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:09,239
But I didn't see--

147
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,657
I-I couldn't see it. I--

148
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,576
[Ellis] It's okay.
It's okay. Hey.

149
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:15,203
- [screams]
- [Ellis] Hey.

150
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,955
Hey, hey, hey.
You're okay. You're okay.

151
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:18,164
We gotta get her out of here.

152
00:08:18,248 --> 00:08:19,624
Baby,
we gotta go, all right?

153
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,459
No. Boyd was here.
Where's Boyd?

154
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:23,962
- I'll find him. Go! Come on.
- We can't leave without him.

155
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,547
Fatima,
we have to go! Come on.

156
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,007
- Ellis!
- Please.

157
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,299
- No. I'm okay. I can--
- Hey.

158
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:30,677
- [shouts in pain]
- Hey! Help me. Hey! Hey!

159
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,388
- [shouts in pain]
- I know, I know.

160
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:36,224
Hey, you're okay.
Come on. Kenny.

161
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,101
But we can't--

162
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:40,729
He's gonna be okay.
He's gonna be okay.

163
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,772
- Come on, baby.
- All right?

164
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:45,108
We gotta go.
We gotta go.

165
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,444
We're gonna be okay.
Come on.

166
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:50,030
It's okay.
Come on. I got you.

167
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:54,409
[Fatima breathing shakily]

168
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:55,368
[Ellis] I got you.

169
00:08:58,663 --> 00:08:59,748
You good?

170
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,751
- Yeah.
- Okay, come on. Let's go.

171
00:09:02,834 --> 00:09:07,005
[wood creaking]

172
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:16,097
[suspenseful music]

173
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:23,813
Boyd?

174
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:45,877
Boyd!

175
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,557
[whispering] Boyd?

176
00:10:21,204 --> 00:10:25,417
Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh.

177
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,585
Hey. Hey. Shh.

178
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:30,171
We gotta get outta here.
Okay?

179
00:10:30,255 --> 00:10:31,214
Okay.

180
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:32,674
We gotta go that way.

181
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:36,302
Hello, Kenny.

182
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,724
It's nice to see you again.

183
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,434
- No.
- [Boyd] Move, move!

184
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:44,227
Now! Move! Go, go!

185
00:10:46,229 --> 00:10:47,981
[breathing heavily]

186
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:49,858
Keep going!
Keep going! Move it!

187
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:52,277
We got it! Keep going!

188
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,779
Come on!
Hurry up.

189
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:56,573
Watch out!

190
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,199
What the fuck?!

191
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:00,285
How?! He didn't--

192
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:01,870
- I know.
- We-- We burned him!

193
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:03,288
- I know.
- We fucking burned him!

194
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:05,331
I know! I know!

195
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:07,167
My God. How did--
how did he even get--

196
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:08,168
The baby.

197
00:11:09,336 --> 00:11:10,670
What?

198
00:11:10,754 --> 00:11:12,839
The baby.

199
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:15,050
I watched it grow.

200
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:17,344
I watched it stand up...

201
00:11:17,427 --> 00:11:19,304
and smile.

202
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:25,435
You're-- you're telling me that
Fatima gave birth to that thing?

203
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,562
Is that what you're saying?

204
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:30,857
Yeah.

205
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,654
- [Donna] You good?
- Yeah, I'm fine. Can you just--

206
00:11:36,738 --> 00:11:38,573
Can you just please
tell me what's going on?

207
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:40,617
- I will.
- Donna!

208
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:46,039
Any word from Boyd yet?

209
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,335
[voices chattering]

210
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:51,795
People are starting
to come back.

211
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:54,589
[footsteps thudding]

212
00:11:54,673 --> 00:11:57,967
- I should go.
- Yeah.

213
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,469
That's probably best.

214
00:12:06,601 --> 00:12:07,727
Donna,
what the fuck is going on?

215
00:12:07,811 --> 00:12:09,062
In here.

216
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,483
[whimpering]

217
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:16,611
[door opens]

218
00:12:16,695 --> 00:12:18,446
Jesus.

219
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:21,366
Hey. Put that down.

220
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,118
She's here to help.

221
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:24,661
Oh, come--
For fuck's sake,

222
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:27,580
we all know it's not loaded!
Just put it away.

223
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:33,336
Now go. You got
nothing else to do here.

224
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:40,593
Fine. Then stay.

225
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:44,014
[sighs]

226
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:45,765
Elgin.

227
00:12:45,849 --> 00:12:47,350
Elgin?

228
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:48,893
Kristi's here to help you.

229
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,437
Can you hear me?

230
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:53,106
I need you
to roll over. Okay?

231
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:55,316
Come on. Come on.

232
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:58,486
- Just careful. Okay.
- There. Come on.

233
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:01,281
Okay, now's the part where
you tell me what happened.

234
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:03,575
Sara took his eye out
with a screwdriver.

235
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:06,953
She had reasons.

236
00:13:07,037 --> 00:13:09,039
- Can you get me a chair?
- Yeah.

237
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:09,998
Okay.

238
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,043
Okay.

239
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,669
Thank you.

240
00:13:16,171 --> 00:13:19,549
Okay, Elgin, can you take
your hand away?

241
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,925
It's okay.

242
00:13:24,596 --> 00:13:26,056
[exhales]

243
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:27,932
[Donna]
Can you stitch him up?

244
00:13:29,768 --> 00:13:32,270
Yeah, I can do my best.

245
00:13:32,354 --> 00:13:33,563
Donna, why--

246
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,023
- Let's talk later.
- [Clara] Donna?

247
00:13:35,106 --> 00:13:36,107
Yes! Just hold on, Clara!

248
00:13:36,191 --> 00:13:37,442
Fatima's back.

249
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:38,735
She and Ellis
are coming up the hill.

250
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:40,028
- Okay, okay.
- What happened?

251
00:13:40,111 --> 00:13:41,821
No, nothing! Nothing!
Back out!

252
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:43,782
- Can I get some ice?
- Yeah. Go!

253
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:53,249
[eerie music]

254
00:13:58,797 --> 00:14:00,840
[exhales]

255
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:15,230
Yeah.

256
00:14:17,941 --> 00:14:22,237
[ominous music]

257
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:29,202
♪

258
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:45,719
Boyd! What--

259
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,387
What--

260
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:49,764
Boyd, what are we doing?

261
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:52,058
Shouldn't... we...

262
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:56,479
[Kenny]
What the fuck is that?

263
00:14:59,816 --> 00:15:01,192
What--

264
00:15:01,276 --> 00:15:04,362
What is it?
What-- Boyd!

265
00:15:12,996 --> 00:15:13,872
Wh--

266
