00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:41,136
- You just need to rest--
- [Fatima] No! I need a shower!

779
00:37:41,219 --> 00:37:44,472
[breathing shakily]

780
00:37:44,556 --> 00:37:47,350
I told you!

781
00:37:47,434 --> 00:37:49,853
I told all of you

782
00:37:49,936 --> 00:37:52,605
that there was something
inside me,

783
00:37:52,689 --> 00:37:54,232
something that...

784
00:37:57,902 --> 00:38:00,405
I begged you to listen!

785
00:38:02,407 --> 00:38:05,160
I don't--
I don't understand what I saw.

786
00:38:05,243 --> 00:38:08,413
I don't know why I saw it.
I didn't--

787
00:38:08,496 --> 00:38:10,457
There's nothing else
I can tell you.

788
00:38:11,624 --> 00:38:13,126
Okay.

789
00:38:13,209 --> 00:38:14,294
I'm sorry.

790
00:38:14,377 --> 00:38:15,337
I'm sorry.

791
00:38:15,420 --> 00:38:17,505
Hey, it's...

792
00:38:29,517 --> 00:38:30,935
Be honest,

793
00:38:31,019 --> 00:38:34,814
what do you think
the chances are he wakes up?

794
00:38:36,316 --> 00:38:40,904
Uh, given how long
he's been out for?

795
00:38:42,405 --> 00:38:43,698
It's not even
so much if he wakes up,

796
00:38:43,782 --> 00:38:45,408
but what kind of shape
he'll be in if he does.

797
00:38:45,492 --> 00:38:46,409
Yeah.

798
00:38:50,413 --> 00:38:52,165
- Kenny?
- Yeah.

799
00:38:52,248 --> 00:38:55,502
Do you have a phone? I, um--
I left mine in the car, and I--

800
00:38:55,585 --> 00:38:57,796
I-I need to call my mom.
She's probably worried sick.

801
00:38:58,922 --> 00:39:01,383
Yeah, um, there's, uh...

802
00:39:01,466 --> 00:39:05,637
There's no...
There's no cell service here.

803
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,055
I could just
go down the hill. It's okay.

804
00:39:07,138 --> 00:39:09,265
I-I don't mean...

805
00:39:09,349 --> 00:39:11,810
I don't mean
here in the clinic.

806
00:39:11,893 --> 00:39:13,186
[Marielle]
I'm gonna go.

807
00:39:14,688 --> 00:39:15,689
I, uh...

808
00:39:15,772 --> 00:39:17,607
What's going on?

809
00:39:17,691 --> 00:39:19,901
I-I need to call my mom.

810
00:39:19,984 --> 00:39:24,280
I know. I understand. I do.

811
00:39:24,364 --> 00:39:28,368
I... I wish I could, um...

812
00:39:29,786 --> 00:39:34,416
We need to have a talk...
about this place

813
00:39:34,499 --> 00:39:37,460
and about that tree
that you saw in the road.

814
00:39:46,469 --> 00:39:47,679
[Julie] Mom.

815
00:39:48,805 --> 00:39:50,932
Where is he?

816
00:39:51,016 --> 00:39:52,851
Why isn't he back yet?

817
00:39:52,934 --> 00:39:54,769
Honey,
your father's fine.

818
00:39:54,853 --> 00:39:56,896
It's not like he's late
coming home from work.

819
00:39:56,980 --> 00:40:00,442
Mom, what happened today?
Why won't you talk to me?

820
00:40:00,525 --> 00:40:02,027
No, Julie, no.
I-I don't wanna talk right now.

821
00:40:02,110 --> 00:40:03,695
- Please!
- I can't.

822
00:40:03,778 --> 00:40:05,155
- Please!
- I can't talk to you.

823
00:40:05,238 --> 00:40:06,740
- I can't talk to you now.
- Stop saying that! Please!

824
00:40:06,823 --> 00:40:09,951
Mom, it's almost dark.
He's not home.

825
00:40:10,035 --> 00:40:11,244
Please, why won't you talk--

826
00:40:11,327 --> 00:40:14,748
[Ethan] Stop it.
Stop yelling at each other.

827
00:40:15,957 --> 00:40:19,169
No, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

828
00:40:20,086 --> 00:40:21,212
- [door closes]
- Is Dad dead?

829
00:40:22,756 --> 00:40:24,090
No!

830
00:40:25,508 --> 00:40:26,801
No, honey. No, he's not.

831
00:40:29,346 --> 00:40:31,806
Maybe he didn't realize
how late it was.

832
00:40:31,890 --> 00:40:33,391
I don't know.

833
00:40:33,475 --> 00:40:38,188
Maybe he's at the Colony House
or the RV.

834
00:40:38,271 --> 00:40:40,148
We'll see him tomorrow.

835
00:40:40,231 --> 00:40:41,941
Well, what if we don't?

836
00:40:44,027 --> 00:40:45,236
Well...

837
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:46,738
Do you remember
what Dad said to us,

838
00:40:46,821 --> 00:40:48,156
the night that Mom
went to the Bottle Tree

839
00:40:48,239 --> 00:40:49,699
and didn't come home?

840
00:40:50,909 --> 00:40:53,536
He said all we have in this
place is what we believe.

841
00:40:53,620 --> 00:40:56,206
So, we have to
believe good things.

842
00:40:56,289 --> 00:40:57,165
Right?

843
00:40:59,084 --> 00:41:00,835
Mom came home.

844
00:41:02,379 --> 00:41:03,588
Dad will, too.

845
00:41:09,135 --> 00:41:13,723
So, um, the monsters, they--
they come every night?

846
00:41:13,807 --> 00:41:15,100
Yeah.

847
00:41:15,183 --> 00:41:19,145
These-- These rocks,
they-- they protect you?

848
00:41:19,229 --> 00:41:21,064
Uh, we call them talismans.

849
00:41:21,147 --> 00:41:22,691
How do they work?

850
00:41:22,774 --> 00:41:25,485
Don't! Don't, um...

851
00:41:25,568 --> 00:41:27,696
Don't take it off the window.

852
00:41:27,779 --> 00:41:29,155
Sorry.

853
00:41:29,239 --> 00:41:31,574
It's okay. It's just, um...

854
00:41:31,658 --> 00:41:34,119
they have to be
hanging for it to work.

855
00:41:34,202 --> 00:41:35,286
Why?

856
00:41:38,289 --> 00:41:39,874
[exhaling sharply]
Uh...

857
00:41:39,958 --> 00:41:42,627
We-- We don't know.

858
00:41:42,711 --> 00:41:43,962
We don't know.

859
00:41:44,045 --> 00:41:47,007
I know how
this must all sound.

860
00:41:47,090 --> 00:41:48,508
"The light shines
in the darkness,

861
00:41:48,591 --> 00:41:50,176
"and the darkness
shall not overcome it."

862
00:41:50,260 --> 00:41:51,886
What is that?

863
00:41:51,970 --> 00:41:53,388
John 1:5.

864
00:41:53,471 --> 00:41:55,682
It means that,
um, God is with us,

865
00:41:55,765 --> 00:41:57,809
even here.

866
00:41:57,892 --> 00:42:01,563
I mean, um, how else can you
explain such a magical thing

867
00:42:01,646 --> 00:42:03,231
to keep the darkness at bay?

868
00:42:05,233 --> 00:42:06,359
Right.

869
00:42:06,443 --> 00:42:08,361
Will you pray
with me, Kenny?

870
00:42:09,738 --> 00:42:11,197
Oh, I'm not--

871
00:42:11,281 --> 00:42:13,158
I'm not really, uh...

872
00:42:13,241 --> 00:42:14,951
I'm not really religious.

873
00:42:15,035 --> 00:42:17,203
That's okay.
God still listens.

874
00:42:18,663 --> 00:42:19,706
Please?

875
00:42:22,417 --> 00:42:24,544
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

876
00:42:28,882 --> 00:42:29,758
[exhaling sharply]

877
00:42:31,426 --> 00:42:34,095
Lord, please protect us
in this dark place,

878
00:42:34,179 --> 00:42:37,349
where evil roams so freely.

879
00:42:37,432 --> 00:42:39,017
Please stand by
my daddy's bedside

880
00:42:39,100 --> 00:42:41,644
and let him wake
renewed in Your love.

881
00:42:41,728 --> 00:42:44,272
And please rest Your hand upon
the shoulders of these people,

882
00:42:44,356 --> 00:42:46,316
trapped here in this place,
who have taken us in

883
00:42:46,399 --> 00:42:48,902
and shown us such kindness.

884
00:42:48,985 --> 00:42:50,403
Be with them tonight,
O Lord,

885
00:42:50,487 --> 00:42:52,781
and let Your love
give them rest.

886
00:42:52,864 --> 00:42:55,450
This we ask in Your name.
Amen.

887
00:42:58,661 --> 00:43:00,121
Uh, Amen.

888
00:43:02,457 --> 00:43:05,251
Um, I'm gonna go sit with
my daddy now, if that's okay.

889
00:43:05,335 --> 00:43:07,379
Yeah. Of course.

890
00:43:51,131 --> 00:43:52,757
There are a lot of people
wanting to know

891
00:43:52,841 --> 00:43:54,676
what happened down there.

892
00:43:56,094 --> 00:43:57,804
Boyd?

893
00:43:57,887 --> 00:43:59,472
You hear what I said?

894
00:43:59,556 --> 00:44:01,266
We had another car today.

895
00:44:03,309 --> 00:44:05,145
A girl and her dad.

896
00:44:06,062 --> 00:44:09,149
Looked like a...
like a pastor, maybe.

897
00:44:11,276 --> 00:44:13,486
He had a--
he had a stroke...

898
00:44:14,738 --> 00:44:17,574
...or a seizure or something.

899
00:44:17,657 --> 00:44:22,203
They crashed into
the Sheriff's Station.

900
00:44:22,287 --> 00:44:24,914
The girl can't be
more than I don't know, 15,

901
00:44:24,998 --> 00:44:27,459
16 years old. She's, uh...

902
00:44:27,542 --> 00:44:29,377
She's up
at the clinic right now,

903
00:44:29,461 --> 00:44:31,588
waiting to see if her dad
lives through the night,

904
00:44:31,671 --> 00:44:33,089
while Kenny explains to her

905
00:44:33,173 --> 00:44:37,218
that whatever life
she had before...

906
00:44:37,302 --> 00:44:38,470
is over,

907
00:44:38,553 --> 00:44:40,430
that, now,
she lives in a place

908
00:44:40,513 --> 00:44:43,475
where monsters smile.

909
00:44:46,519 --> 00:44:48,438
That girl's probably
gonna die here.

910
00:44:48,521 --> 00:44:50,482
- Boyd!
- You know,

911
00:44:50,565 --> 00:44:53,943
the only thing that gets me
out of bed in the morning

912
00:44:54,027 --> 00:44:57,238
is the idea that...

913
00:44:57,322 --> 00:45:01,326
maybe, just-- just maybe,
we can beat this place,

914
00:45:01,409 --> 00:45:04,537
that maybe we can get
everybody home,

915
00:45:04,621 --> 00:45:06,706
that, someday, maybe

916
00:45:06,790 --> 00:45:11,211
the good guys actually win!

917
00:45:11,294 --> 00:45:14,381
And then I saw that
fucking thing in the tunnels!

918
00:45:14,464 --> 00:45:17,634
The same goddamn smile--
that same...

919
00:45:17,717 --> 00:45:19,511
And I realized--

920
00:45:19,594 --> 00:45:22,138
I mean, this place has been
three steps ahead of us

921
00:45:22,222 --> 00:45:23,640
from the beginning!

922
00:45:23,723 --> 00:45:25,600
Just like you said,
the game's rigged.

923
00:45:25,684 --> 00:45:27,477
Doesn't matter what we do.

924
00:45:27,560 --> 00:45:29,646
Doesn't matter
what we sacrifice.

925
00:45:29,729 --> 00:45:33,900
None of it means
a goddamn thing if we can't--

926
00:45:33,983 --> 00:45:35,068
Hey, where you going?

927
00:45:35,151 --> 00:45:37,737
I am not going anywhere.

928
00:45:37,821 --> 00:45:40,156
None of us are.

929
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:41,950
Okay, no, fuck this.

930
00:45:42,033 --> 00:45:43,743
Get out of my way, Kristi!

931
00:45:43,827 --> 00:45:45,745
No, no.
You don't get to do this.

932
00:45:45,829 --> 00:45:47,497
It's a pretty
shit time for you

933
00:45:47,580 --> 00:45:48,540
to start feeling sorry
for yourself.

934
00:45:48,623 --> 00:45:49,958
Oh, is that what I'm doing?

935
00:45:50,041 --> 00:45:51,626
Yeah, you are!

936
00:45:51,710 --> 00:45:53,753
And you have plenty
of reasons to.

937
00:45:53,837 --> 00:45:56,923
So does everybody else here.
But none of those people

938
00:45:57,007 --> 00:45:59,342
are asking me to stitch up
people's eye sockets,

939
00:45:59,426 --> 00:46:01,469
so I'm gonna need
a little more from you

940
00:46:01,553 --> 00:46:02,929
than "These monsters
live forever,

941
00:46:03,013 --> 00:46:05,181
"so we're all gonna die."

942
00:46:05,265 --> 00:46:06,850
Because it doesn't matter
how many people

943
00:46:06,933 --> 00:46:08,309
I stitch back up together,

944
00:46:08,393 --> 00:46:10,228
if they see you lose faith,

945
00:46:10,311 --> 00:46:11,980
then that's
when people start

946
00:46:12,063 --> 00:46:13,440
hanging themselves
in the bathroom.

947
00:46:14,983 --> 00:46:17,193
Can you guys
give us a second?

948
00:46:18,361 --> 00:46:19,487
Yeah.

949
00:46:19,571 --> 00:46:21,489
[Donna] Let's go.

950
00:46:21,573 --> 00:46:23,199
[clears throat]

951
00:46:23,283 --> 00:46:24,284
Let's go.

952
00:46:41,343 --> 00:46:43,219
Kristi's right, Dad.

953
00:46:44,888 --> 00:46:47,515
Look, no matter what happens,

954
00:46:47,599 --> 00:46:51,269
you are the one person
that nobody here can see...

955
00:46:53,980 --> 00:46:56,483
- Dad!
- I can't do it anymore.

956
00:46:56,566 --> 00:46:58,943
Ellis, I can't!

957
00:46:59,027 --> 00:47:00,445
I'm falling apart!

958
00:47:03,782 --> 00:47:08,620
Everything I've done,
every sacrifice we've made,

959
00:47:08,703 --> 00:47:11,664
and if--
if I can't get you home,

960
00:47:11,748 --> 00:47:14,209
then none of it matters!
Your mom?!

961
00:47:14,292 --> 00:47:15,835
Your mom?!

962
00:47:15,919 --> 00:47:16,795
It's...

963
00:47:18,421 --> 00:47:20,090
Fuck,
it can't be for nothing!

964
00:47:20,173 --> 00:47:21,508
I just-- I...

965
00:47:21,591 --> 00:47:24,886
[voice breaking]
I can't fucking...

966
00:47:24,969 --> 00:47:28,223
I cannot...

967
00:47:28,306 --> 00:47:30,225
any...

968
00:47:30,308 --> 00:47:31,309
God.

969
00:47:31,393 --> 00:47:36,314
[sobbing]

970
00:47:36,398 --> 00:47:38,024
[Ellis] I know.

971
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:40,694
I know.

972
00:47:40,777 --> 00:47:42,821
[sobbing]

973
00:47:54,416 --> 00:47:57,085
[metallic clattering]

974
00:47:58,503 --> 00:48:00,922
What was that?

975
00:48:01,006 --> 00:48:02,173
I don't know.

976
00:48:04,509 --> 00:48:04,801
Mom?

977
00:48:07,846 --> 00:48:11,766
[suspenseful music]

978
00:48:40,628 --> 00:48:46,343
♪

979
00:48:46,426 --> 00:48:47,427
What's happening?

980
00:49:37,727 --> 00:49:41,981
[breathing deeply]

981
00:49:46,194 --> 00:49:47,237
Wake up.

982
00:49:53,284 --> 00:49:54,536
That's better.

983
00:49:56,329 --> 00:49:58,540
Blink twice
if you can hear me.

984
00:50:01,459 --> 00:50:04,129
I know this must be
very confusing for you.

985
00:50:04,212 --> 00:50:06,923
But it's important
you understand

986
00:50:07,007 --> 00:50:11,970
that you played a very special
role in a very important story.

987
00:50:21,771 --> 00:50:24,691
You see, um...

988
00:50:24,774 --> 00:50:27,235
I couldn't've come
to them as I was.

989
00:50:31,614 --> 00:50:34,993
[exhales, laughs]

990
00:50:35,076 --> 00:50:37,787
[Sophia] Not with everything 
they learned.

991
00:50:45,920 --> 00:50:49,466
[groaning]

992
00:50:49,549 --> 00:50:53,887
[groaning continues]

993
00:50:55,680 --> 00:50:58,016
- [groaning]
- [cracking]

994
00:50:58,099 --> 00:51:01,102
[groaning]

995
00:51:01,186 --> 00:51:02,854
[bones cracking]

996
00:51:02,937 --> 00:51:04,939
[groaning]

997
00:51:05,023 --> 00:51:08,860
[bones cracking]

998
00:51:08,943 --> 00:51:10,320
[groaning]

999
00:51:10,403 --> 00:51:13,865
[feminine groaning]

1000
00:51:13,948 --> 00:51:17,494
[bones cracking]

1001
00:51:30,548 --> 00:51:32,967
What's happening
to you isn't fair.

1002
00:51:44,562 --> 00:51:45,689
Are you all right?

1003
00:51:45,772 --> 00:51:47,107
I'm lost.

1004
00:51:47,190 --> 00:51:48,483
Me too.

1005
00:51:49,567 --> 00:51:51,319
Would you like a ride?

1006
00:51:54,322 --> 00:51:56,074
When you stopped for me,

1007
00:51:56,157 --> 00:51:58,284
I know you did so
with kindness in your heart.

1008
00:52:04,249 --> 00:52:05,250
[gasps]

1009
00:52:08,378 --> 00:52:10,046
[engine revving]

1010
00:52:11,339 --> 00:52:12,757
[engine revving]

1011
00:52:12,841 --> 00:52:14,300
[tires screeching]

1012
00:52:16,052 --> 00:52:19,514
You must be so afraid.

1013
00:52:19,597 --> 00:52:22,392
I'm sorry you won't be here
to see what comes next.

1014
00:52:23,643 --> 00:52:25,603
It's always
my favorite part.

1015
00:52:28,106 --> 00:52:30,692
It's the part I wish
could last forever.

1016
00:52:32,444 --> 00:52:33,820
Would you like to know why?

1017
00:52:39,909 --> 00:52:43,121
This is when
they tear themselves apart.

1018
00:52:46,458 --> 00:52:48,376
[muffled grunting]

1019
00:52:48,460 --> 00:52:50,462
[grunting continues]

1020
00:52:57,802 --> 00:53:04,684
♪
